org.jcvi.jillion.fasta

Interface FastaVisitor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultQualityFastaFileDataStoreBuilder

    public interface FastaVisitor
    FastaVisitor is a visitor interface to visit components of a single fasta file.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

    • Method Detail

      • visitDefline

        FastaRecordVisitor visitDefline(FastaVisitorCallback callback,
                                String id,
                                String optionalComment)
        Visit the definition line of the current fasta record.
        Parameters:
        callback - a FastaVisitorCallback that can be used to communicate with the parser object.
        id - the id of this record as a String
        optionalComment - the comment for this record. This comment may have white space. If no comment exists, then this parameter will be null.
        Returns:
        an instance of FastaRecordVisitor; if this method returns null, then that means to skip the current record.

      • visitEnd

        void visitEnd()
        Visit the end of the fasta file.

      • halted

        void halted()
        The parser has stopped parsing the fasta file due to FastaVisitorCallback.haltParsing() being called. The end of the fasta file was not yet reached.
